---
// src/pages/terms.astro
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const lastUpdated = "July 6, 2026";
---

<Base
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="The terms you agree to when using PatreonTV."
>
  <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
  <p style="color: var(--text-dim);">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

  <h2>Who we are</h2>
  <p>
    PatreonTV is an independent, open-source Apple TV client for viewing
    Patreon content you already have access to. We are not affiliated
    with, endorsed by, or sponsored by Patreon Inc.
  </p>

  <h2>The service</h2>
  <p>
    PatreonTV is provided as a native tvOS application. It is a
    <strong>viewer</strong> for content on your Patreon account — it
    does not itself host, sell, or distribute the content of any
    creator. All content viewed through PatreonTV remains subject to
    Patreon's own Terms of Use and the individual creators' terms.
  </p>

  <h2>Your Patreon account</h2>
  <p>
    You must have a Patreon account to use PatreonTV. You sign in on
    patreon.com from your phone or computer during device pairing — we
    never see your password. Your session cookie is delivered to your
    Apple TV through our pairing service (encrypted, short-lived, deleted
    after delivery), stored in the tvOS Keychain on your device, and used
    to authenticate requests to Patreon on your behalf.
  </p>

  <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>You agree not to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Attempt to circumvent Patreon's paywall or view content you have not
      paid to access.
    </li>
    <li>
      Redistribute, rebroadcast, or otherwise re-publish content viewed
      through PatreonTV. The license you receive as a paying patron is for
      your own private, personal, non-commercial viewing.
    </li>
    <li>
      Reverse-engineer, decompile, or attempt to derive the source code of
      PatreonTV in ways that violate its MIT license.
    </li>
    <li>Use PatreonTV in a way that violates Patreon's own Terms of Use.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Payments</h2>
  <p>
    PatreonTV is free. It does not process payments and does not sell
    subscriptions or memberships. To join a creator's tier or change your
    pledge, use Patreon's website or their official iOS app, subject to
    the applicable Apple in-app purchase rules where they apply.
  </p>

  <h2>Availability & changes</h2>
  <p>
    PatreonTV depends on Patreon's own systems to function. If Patreon
    changes its API, blocks third-party clients, or is otherwise
    unavailable, PatreonTV may not work as expected. We may release
    updates, change features, or discontinue the app at our discretion.
  </p>

  <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
  <p>
    PatreonTV is provided <strong>as is, without warranty of any kind</strong>,
    express or implied, including but not limited to the warranties of
    merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and
    non-infringement. We do not warrant that the app will be uninterrupted,
    error-free, or that any content will be available.
  </p>

  <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the maximum extent permitted by law, in no event will PatreonTV or
    its contributors be liable for any indirect, incidental, special,
    consequential, or punitive damages arising out of or related to your
    use of the app.
  </p>

  <h2>Governing law</h2>
  <p>
    These terms are governed by the laws of the United States. Disputes
    that cannot be resolved informally will be handled in the state or
    federal courts located there.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about these terms? Reach us at
    <a href="/support">support</a>.
  </p>
</Base>
